                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notAfter="1825" notBefore="1800">
                        <p>Typical Holkham binding of light brown leather, with Coke family ostrich crest in gilt in the centre of the upper cover. Date: early nineteenth century. Rebound by <persName key="person_707" role="bnd">John Jones</persName> of Liverpool (worked for Holkham 1816–1823). The spine lettered in gilt: HOMILIÆ/SELECTÆ/ GR./–M.S./ SÆC. XII./ in pasted black leather: MS. /HOLKHAM/ Gr. /41.</p>
                     </binding>
